column8: Large water park, great for the summer if you live near Concord. There are pools, slides and 8 different rides. Most rides require a height limit of 48 inches. Two separate waterplay playgrounds for the under 48 inches crowd. Consider a seaonal pass to get more value.

Enjoy a fun day with the family at this 135 acres theme park. The park has diverse rides from pulse-pounding roller coasters to gentler options for tots. Their animal program offers unique opportunities to meet animals truly up-close and personal. In addition to the most thrilling rides you'll find a wide variety of top-shelf entertainment and fresh prepared to order and ready to thrill your taste buds.

The Boardwalk combines the attraction of the California beach with the thrills of an amusement park. It  offers kiddie and family rids as well as many attractions such as a mini golf and a boardwalk bowl.

Great America provides a great choice for family fun and adventure! There is something for everyone. From the many rides and attractions to a water park or even a planet snoopy for the young at heart.  Don’t miss the live entertainment and the daily special events. Be minded for the long lines on the popular rides.
With close to 40 storybook sets, kid-size rides, 15 domestic friendly animals, and 10 acres of gardens, the park is especially designed for kids under age eight.

The Musée Mécanique is an interesting place if you enjoy seeing the games through the years. It contains over 300 mechanical machines all operating, and is one of the largest privately owned collections of such games in the world.

The place is small and contains only 7 rides, but it's perfect for little kids, and you don't need to walk far to go to other rides. It's cheap as there is no entrance fee, you buy the tickets ride and you don't need to pay park.

At Small World Amusement Park you will find activities for the whole family. From the small pond with catch and release crawdad fishing with a boat that has been converted to a play structure to the many rides including  a train ride, steam boat play, a carousel, a fort, a balloon ride, a Humphrey the Whale ride, playgrounds, an insect barn, as well as a butterfly terrarium.

This park offers over 40 rides and exhibitions in a beautiful garden setting. Many unique fruit and vegetable themed rides for small and bigger kids plus a roller coaster, railroads, and boat ride. Exhibits include a collection of world famous Circus Trees, a rock maze, and the Learning Sheds as well as a six majestic gardensthroughout the park. For the young at heart don’t miss the Oak Park playground.
